data.chText: （相同种族或背景人的）聚居区；贫民区
data.enText: an area of a city where many people of the same race or background live, separately from the rest of the population. Ghettos are often crowded, with bad living conditions.

data.chText: 在贫民区长大的穷孩子
data.enText: a poor kid growing up in the ghetto

data.chText: 西班牙南海岸可以说已经成为旅游者的聚居区。
data.enText: The south coast of Spain has become something of a tourist ghetto.

data.chText: （昔日城市中的）犹太人居住区
data.enText: the area of a town where Jews were forced to live in the past

means: (相同种族或背景人的)聚居区
(昔日城市中的)犹太人居住区

tr: a poor densely populated city district occupied by a minority ethnic group linked together by economic hardship and social restrictions
formerly the restricted quarter of many European cities in which Jews were required to live
any segregated mode of living or working that results from bias or stereotyping
example: the relative security of the gay ghetto
no escape from the ghetto of the typing pool

value.def: A ghetto is a part of a city in which many poor people or many people of a particular race, religion, or nationality live separately from everyone else.

example.ex: ...the black ghettos of New York and Los Angeles.
example.tran: 纽约和洛杉矶的黑人聚居区

example.ex: ...the gang kids who will never escape the ghetto.
example.tran: 永远无法走出贫民区的帮派少年

value.tran: 贫民区；（相同种族、宗教或国籍的人的）聚居区

trans: 大型手提式收录机(或激光唱机)
